==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Harem
<hw>Ha"rem</hw> <pr>(h⟦amac⟧"r⟦ecr⟧m; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos><ety>[Ar.
<ets>haram</ets>, orig., anything forbidden or sacred, fr.
<ets>harama</ets> to forbid, prohibit.]</ety> <ety>[Written also
<ets>haram</ets> and <ets>hareem</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
apartments or portion of the house allotted to females in Muslim
families.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The family of wives and concubines belonging to one
man, in Muslim countries; a seraglio.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Harengiform</ent>⟦br⟧
